y DeVito, {{CBSB link|year=2018|team=Seton Hall Pirates|title=Seton Hall}} || [[Ed Blankmeyer]], St. John's<ref name=\"Big East awards\"/>{{efn|group=cw|The Big East awards a Coaching Staff of the Year award instead of a Coach of the Year award. It goes to the team instead of an individual, although the head coach is cited by name in the award announcement.}} || [[2018 Big East Conference Baseball Tournament]] || [[Prasco Park]] \u2022 [[Mason, Ohio|Mason, OH]] || St. John's\n|-\n|[[Big South Conference]] || {{CBSB link|year=2018|team=Campbell Fighting Camels|title=Campbell}} || Austin Zente, {{CBSB link|year=2018|team=High Point Panthers|title=High Point}}<ref name=\"Big South awards\">{{cite press release|url=http://bigsouthsports.com/news/2018/5/22/big-south-announces-2018-baseball-annual-award-winners.aspx |title=Big South Announces 2018 Baseball Annual Award Winners |publisher=Big South Conference |date=May 22, 2018 |accessdate=June 7, 2018}}</ref> || Allan Winans, Campbell<ref name=\"Big South awards\"/> || [[Justin Haire]], Campbell<ref name=\"Big South awards\"/> || [[2018 Big South Conference Baseball Tournament]] || [[Liberty Baseball Stadium]] \u2022 [[Lynchburg, Virginia|Lynchburg, VA]] || Campbell\n|-\n|[[Big Ten Conference]] || {{CBSB link|year=2018|team=Minnesota Golden Gophers|title=Minnesota}} || [[Bren Spillane]], [[2018 Illinois Fighting Illini baseball team|Illinois]]<ref name=\"B1G awards\">{{cite press release |url=http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-basebl/spec-rel/052218aaa.html |title=Big Ten Announces Baseball All-Big Ten Honors and Individual Award Winners |publisher=Big Ten Conference |date=May 22, 2018 |accessdate=June 7, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612141630/http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-basebl/spec-rel/052218aaa.html |archive-date=2018-06-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref> || Patrick Fredrickson, Minnesota<ref name=\"B1G awards\"/> || [[John Anderson (baseball coach)|John Anderson]], Minnesota<ref name=\"B1G awards\"/> || 